comment:
Amber Heard was granted a *TEMPORARY* restraining order.  She was required to produce *NO EVIDENCE*, and *Mr. Depp was not informed of the order.*  Temporary restraining orders provide protection for a short period of time (usually two weeks), *until a Judge can hear the evidence for the case* of a regular restraining order.  When Ms. Heard presented her evidence, the Judge *DISMISSED THE CASE WITH PREJUDICE!*  This means that he found Ms. Heard's case to be "egregiously flawed, and without merit."  It also means Ms. Heard can *never bring these charges against Mr. Depp in the future.*  Ms. Heard presents this restraining order as if it "means something".  It means that *her evidence was SO FLAWED, the Judge threw it out permanently.*

Does Amber Heard want equal rights for women?  If Mr. Depp loses his employment during *ongoing* litigation *demanding a RE-TRIAL* because Judge Nicol did not disclose that *HIS SON worked WITH DAN WOOTON, and FOR Rupert Murdoch, who OWNS "THE SUN" ...the two defendants that Mr. Depp is suing,* then why is Ms. Heard, who was arrested for the uncontested domestic assault of her then wife, Tasya van Ree, in 2009, at the Seattle/Tacoma International Airport, employed to play Mera? 

You state that Amber Heard was revealed, in the tapes that SHE made, to be an abuser *AS WELL!*  This is untrue.  She is revealed to be *the ONLY ABUSER*.  Mr. Depp never admits to abuse.  Mr. Depp never apologizes for abuse.  In fact, Ms. Heard *CLEARLY STATES on multiple occasions that Mr. Depp "ALWAYS LEAVES" when she becomes physical during their fights.*  THAT is what she is angry about.  She says that he doesn't "care enough to stay and FIGHT for their marriage".  She disparagingly calls Mr. Depp "the bigger person" and mockingly says "you're the more honorable one" as though that indicates something bad.
     *Johnny Depp*  "If things get physical, we *have* to separate..."
     *Amber Heard*  "No, we don't."
     *Johnny Depp*  "We have to be apart from one another.  Whether it's for an hour, or ten hours, or a day.  We must.  There can be no physical violence."
     *Amber Heard*  "I can't promise you that I'll be perfect.  I can't promise you that I won't get physical again.  God, I f------ sometimes get so mad...I lose it."

Ms. Heard saying "paid rumors, and paid campaigns on social media don't dictate, because they have no basis in reality." is laughable, as the Judge in the Virginia Trial *dismissed her claims that these petitions were "paid",* while insisting that the claims that Ms. Heard made in multiple press releases, that she donated her settlement to charity, must be proven by the necessary paperwork by the charities in question...leading to the startling revelation from the Children's Hospital of Los Angeles that *there is no paperwork for any donations made by Amber Heard of her settlement money!*  While she is busy accusing others of lying, she has broken California Law by making public statements that she donated 3.5 million dollars to CHLA when she has not.

Emelia Clark is a lovely, talented actress, who is good friends with Jason Momoa, and has excellent chemistry with him.  Amber Heard is a domestic abuser, currently facing trial for defamation in the United States.  She is a documented, confessed liar (having pleaded Guilty to lying on Official Australian Documents pertaining to smuggling her two tea-cup Yorkies into Australia).  She knew this would put the dogs at risk of being euthanized, as rabies diagnoses requires the forensic examination of the brain, so she isn't much of a pet lover.  Ms. Heard is also in the process of facing further charges of subornation of perjury in Australia, as a result of the British "Sun" Trial.  Most recently, the Virginia Case disclosure has revealed that Ms. Heard did not donate her divorce settlement money to charity.  At the conclusion of the Virginia Trial, Ms. Heard and her team of co-conspirators will be facing a group of charges in California for crimes committed there, and Mr. Depp has petitioned for a completely new trial in Britain...and as Judge Nicol cited Ms. Heard's donation of her settlement to charity *IN* his verdict...it looks good for a re-trial.  Ms. Heard's crimes aside, she will be tied up in litigation for a considerable time.
